FBIS3-23079 "jptot010__l94041" JPRS-TOT-94-010-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ALGERIA Three Police Hijack Airliner, Seek Asylum in Spain Twelve Passengers Released LD2802154294 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1500 GMT 28 Feb 94 LD2802154294 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] [passage omitted] Concha Flores reports from Alicante airport. Good afternoon. [Flores] Good afternoon. It appears that there are developments taking place right now, namely that the women and children who were aboard the Air Algerie Boeing 727 may be disembarking. This is a report that we have just received and cannot be confirmed because of how far away the aircraft is being held on the runway -- quite a long way from the central installations of l'Altet airport. [passage omitted] The extensive police deployment has not affected the normal functioning of the airport, where flights are still arriving and leaving. The base of operations is in the control tower where they are being headed by Civil Governor Alfonso Calve, along with the provincial chief inspector, the acting Civil Guard chief, the recently appointed Algerian consul in Alicante, who took up his post this morning, and a military member from the Alcantarilla base. [Madrid Teletexto TVE in Spanish at 1525 GMT on 28 February reports that: "Eight women, two men, and two children have left the hijacked Algerian aircraft, which landed at Alicante airport.]
